Stavroula Tsolakidou vs Mrudul Dehankar
World Junior Girls Championship (2019), New Delhi, India, rd 4, Oct-16 
Caro-Kann, exchange variation (B13)

IMPORTANT UPDATE!!! 
It seems the PGN was incorrect on all websites. The Mysterious Queen Sac never happened. After publishing the video, I was contacted by several subscribers with this video.
Watch the interview with Dehankar and how the game actually went on Chessbase India's Channel here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M-9AEYsmrWk&feature=youtu.be&fbclid=IwAR3uemWO3sGD35IDsOr-_i5OWpkJ9aM0u8G-s0oz3rVpnBk8xrc0htRakWQ

The World Junior Girls Championship is an 11-round Swiss tournament taking place from 15-25 October 2019 in New Delhi, India.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, plus a 30-second increment starting from move one. Official website: www.worldjuniorchess2019.com
